<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861222-0183 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Niagara Mohawk Power Corp.</HL><DD> 12/22/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> NMKSTOCK MARKET, OFFERINGS (STK) </IN><TEXT>   NIAGARA MOHAWK POWER CORP. sold three million shares of 8 3/4% preferred stock at $25 each, Salomon Brothers Inc., head underwriter, said. The shares have a mandatory sinking fund that will retire 20% of the shares each year beginning in 1992. The Syracuse, N.Y.-based electric and gas utility will use proceeds to finance its construction program and reduce short-term debt. </TEXT></DOC>